  <!--
    In this component configuration, an example session pooling repository is defined.
    By default, session of the pooling repository is refreshed on every passivating phase.
    However, if the 'refreshOnPassivate' property is false in the following example, 
    then the session of the pooling repository is refreshed on an specified event by an event listener.
    The event listener defined here tries to refresh every session on the specified events.
    
    In the following example, the following properties should be defined in your configuration files:
      - 'event.based.repository.address'
      - 'event.based.repository.user.name'
      - 'event.based.repository.password'
    
    If you want to use the following components for some reasons, please uncomment the followings.
  -->
  
  
